[1] UK (HPA)
Date: Fri 24 Feb 2012
Source: HPA (Health Protection Agency (HPA) Weekly Report [abbreviated & edited]
http://www.hpa.org.uk/hpr/archives/2012/news0812.htm#msls1201

Measles cases in England and Wales: update to end-January 2012
-------------------------------------------------------
The number of confirmed cases of measles in England and Wales with an onset date in January 2012 continues the decline observed at the end of 2011; only 37 cases were confirmed in January 2012 compared to 66 and 57 cases respectively for November and December 2011. The majority of cases reported in January were from the South East region. On-going investigations into a cluster of cases in the Liverpool area and a second unlinked cluster in North Wales [see following report] suggest that there will be a rise in confirmed cases during February.

A total of 1086 laboratory confirmed measles cases were reported in England and Wales in 2011, compared to 380 in 2010 and 1,144 in 2009. The highest numbers of confirmed cases were reported in London and South East regions. In the last two years there has been a shift to cases occurring in older children (>14 years) and adults; around 40% in both 2010 and 2011 compared to just under 20% in 2009. In 2011, 14% of cases were associated with recent travel or household contact with individuals recently returning from travel abroad.

