[6] India (Bhopal)
Date: Sun 26 Feb 2012
Source: Times of India, Bhopal [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhopal/Measles-outbreak-in-Nalkheda-village/articleshow/12039691.cms

Measles outbreak in Nalkheda village
-------------------------------
BHOPAL: With the advent of summer season, measles cases in the city have hit a yearly high. Fifty children were administered care after the disease was reported from Nalkheda village in Berasia here on Saturday [25 Feb 2012]

According to district chief medical and health officer (CMHO) Dr Pankaj Shulka, "About 50 children are suffering from measles in the village and an emergency team has been formed to tackle the outbreak of the disease." Health officials collected blood samples from the nearby areas after the CHMO visited the village on Saturday [25 Feb 2012]. However, according to the health workers, the cases of measles were not severe among the children as they had been immunised previously [presumably with a single dose of vaccine - Mod.CP]. Health officials said that measures are in place to bring the disease under control. Parents have been meanwhile asked to keep the affected children away from school. "This will prevent spreading of disease to other students," said a local resident.

